				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: You, the server tick, aggro, and you<a name="67662"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 7:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually no, it is about every 6 seconds, on the server tick that it gets checked but if there is any kind of lag on client or server side it will display differently on your screen.
<br />

<br />
You need to give up to a 2 second margin on either side if you have a connection (or for Xegony a server) that is not too good.
<br />

<br />
When you have no server side or client side hiccups (steady connection that is) you should see the 6 second server tick check, if not there will be a slight variation.
<br />

<br />
Use regen and a small dot to check the server tick and then find a mob that you know the agro range of.
<br />
It will almost exactly a fraction after the server tick agro you if you do a small dash in.
<br />
Main reason it is not checked every two seconds is that if you run over a mob you don't allways agro it (pof amy warrior in my case) on the spot and can sometimes get far enough to not get agroed.
<br />
Now given the agro range on those things you are looking at more then 2 seconds there for checks when using just base selo's chorus when running up and past them.
<br />

<br />
The thing with the necro and the invis click  is that it needs to be received by the server too or the server just says tough luck and agroes you which means cutting it fine on a second before the server tick might not be received on time for the server so you don't get agro.
<br />

<br />
Purely on time used from getting up and clicking you are talking about two and a bit seconds here so you have a a margin of only a second or so on either side.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
