				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: You, the server tick, proximity aggro, and you<a name="67695"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 12:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm on Xegony AND on a bad connection, so make what you will of this.
<br />

<br />
When (most) mobs turn green or light blue to me, they will prox agro only on a server tick, and only when very close to them.  Many dark blue mobs seem to only prox agro on server ticks.  (Possibly true for all LDoN mobs?)
<br />

<br />
Many con even or higher mobs, and some special mobs will prox agro much more frequently.
<br />

<br />
At level &lt;20ish, compare the amount of time it takes skeletons and higher level Burynai in the basement of Kurn's towers to prox agro you with the time it takes lower level Burynai.
<br />

<br />
At level &lt;55ish, compare how quickly the wolf and grimling guards just outside of Acrylia caverns agro with how quickly the grimling caves elsewhere agro.
<br />

<br />
Not sure of any good examples for level 70ish.  
<br />

<br />
Skyfire is a good place to notice agro only on a tick, though at 70 you may need to sit to get agro at all.
<br />

<br />
I can easily pop my head around a corner in KT, start HoS on a mob, and pop back without getting proximity agro.  Hard to say whether this is because of server ticks, or if it is because being on a modem makes it hard for the mob to realize I was in line of sight.
<br />

<br />
I have, in many places, proximity agroed, faded, reagroed, refaded in the course of much less than 6 seconds. 
<br />

<br />
And for the silliest example of prox agro I've encountered, though it may have been changed in the past four years:
<br />
In Ogguk if you are appropriate level, threatening mobs have a larger agro radius than kill on sight mobs.  If you are barely KoS and hit a guard with charismatic carillion from max range, it will become threatening and pretty much immediately agro.  If you let them remain KoS, you can dodge guards all the way to the bank.
<br />

<br />
Lall
<br />
Bold Bardess with 117 Melodic Tools
<br />
Shards of Avalon, Xegony.</span></td>
