				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: You, the server tick, proximity aggro, and you<a name="67730"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 21 04 5:15 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Thanks for all the replies.  I've noticed the longer prox aggro time for greenies too, and the fact that you have to stand right on top of them practically before they will aggro.  So the rules about prox aggro are not rigid.
<br />

<br />
My original experiment was this:
<br />

<br />
I walked up next to a blue conning guard just outside of Neriak.  I was singing invis and then just stopped the song (didn't click it off... just stopped singing it).  12-18 seconds later, the invis finally drops, due to the server tick, and invariably withn 1 to 2 seconds I'd get aggro.
<br />

<br />
So I'm guessing there's a finer tick, or perhaps aggro gets checked more often if you are closer to the mob.  I was standing right next to him at the time... within bad breath distance (stinky dark elf breath).
<br />

<br />
Maybe a good next experiment would be to try the same thing at max prox aggro range and see if the time varies.
<br />

<br />
