				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: You, the server tick, proximity aggro, and you<a name="67756"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 22 04 5:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There is timer-based aggro, and event-driven aggro. The former is epitomised by the way mobs will pnly aggro on the server tick if you walk within range of them. An example of the latter is a mob's &quot;call for help&quot; when you do get aggro. We (the players) probably do not know the full list of events that trigger aggro like this, and it may vary by expansion.
